@namespace MyPortfolio_Anna.Pages.ProjectCases
@page "/projects/document-generation-service"
@layout CaseStudyLayout

<Header>
    <h1>Automated Document Generation Service</h1>
    <p>
        A reusable backend service for generating invoices and delivery notes
        with strict layout requirements, multi-copy output,
        and secure cloud-based document storage.
    </p>

    <CaseStudyTechStack Items="TechStack" />
</Header>

<CaseStudySection Title="Problem">
    Business-critical documents such as invoices and delivery notes
    were previously generated manually or through inconsistent templates.
    This resulted in formatting errors, layout drift, and increased effort
    when supporting multiple document types and copies.
</CaseStudySection>

<CaseStudySection Title="Constraints">
    <ul>
        <li>Strict layout requirements matching existing financial templates</li>
        <li>Support for multiple document types and variants</li>
        <li>Multi-copy output per document (e.g. customer, internal)</li>
        <li>Documents must be securely stored and retrievable</li>
    </ul>
</CaseStudySection>

<CaseStudySection Title="Solution">
    Designed a reusable document generation engine
    that programmatically renders PDF documents
    using precise layout control, supports multiple document variants,
    and integrates with cloud storage for secure access and distribution.
</CaseStudySection>

<CaseStudyArchitecture
    Description="
        The service operates as a backend module where
        application services prepare structured document data,
        the PDF generation layer renders layouts using PDFSharp,
        and Azure Blob Storage securely stores generated files
        with controlled access for downstream systems.
    " />

<CaseStudyOutcomes Items="Outcomes" />

<CaseStudySection Title="Key Technical Decisions">
    <ul>
        <li>Code-driven layout rendering to eliminate template drift</li>
        <li>Separation of document structure and data preparation</li>
        <li>Reusable helpers for consistent spacing, fonts, and tables</li>
        <li>Cloud storage integration to avoid filesystem dependencies</li>
    </ul>
</CaseStudySection>

<CaseStudySection Title="What I’d Improve Next">
    Introduce asynchronous document generation for large batches,
    add template versioning support,
    and expose document previews for user verification
    before final generation.
</CaseStudySection>

